{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6210b36b-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"47"},"text":"§ 47.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Employment of Indian labor and purchase of products of Indian industry; participation in Mentor-Protege Program","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6210b36c-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b36d-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Indian economic enterprise","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “Indian economic enterprise” has the meaning given the term in section 1480.201 of title 48, Code of Federal Regulations (or successor regulations).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b36e-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Mentor firm; protege firm","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The terms “mentor firm” and “protege firm” have the meanings given those terms in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s4902/c"},"text":"section 4902(c) of title 10","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b36f-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Secretaries","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “Secretaries” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b370-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/a/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary of the Interior; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b371-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/a/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary of Health and Human Services.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6210b372-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Enterprise Development","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b373-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Unless determined by one of the Secretaries to be impracticable and unreasonable—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b374-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Indian labor shall be employed; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b375-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" purchases of Indian industry products (including printing and facilities construction, notwithstanding any other provision of law) may be made in open market by the Secretaries.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b376-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Mentor-protege program","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b377-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Participation in the Mentor-Protege Program established under section 831(a) of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 1991 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2302"},"text":"10 U.S.C. 2302","children":[],"tail":" note; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/510"},"text":"Public Law 101–510","children":[],"tail":") or receipt of assistance under a developmental assistance agreement under that program shall not render any individual or entity involved in the provision of Indian labor or an Indian industry product ineligible to receive assistance under this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b378-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Treatment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this section, no determination of affiliation or control (whether direct or indirect) may be found between a protege firm and a mentor firm on the basis that the mentor firm has provided, or agreed to provide, to the protege firm, pursuant to a mentor-protege agreement, any form of developmental assistance described in section 831(f) of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 1991 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2302"},"text":"10 U.S.C. 2302","children":[],"tail":" note; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/510"},"text":"Public Law 101–510","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6210b379-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Implementation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In carrying out this section, the Secretaries shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b37a-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" conduct outreach to Indian industrial entities;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b37b-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provide training;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b37c-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" promulgate regulations in accordance with this section and with the regulations under part 1480 of title 48, Code of Federal Regulations (or successor regulations), to harmonize the procurement procedures of the Department of the Interior and the Department of Health and Human Services, to the maximum extent practicable;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b37d-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/c/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" require regional offices of the Bureau of Indian Affairs and the Indian Health Service to aggregate data regarding compliance with this section;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b37e-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/c/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" require procurement management reviews by their respective Departments to include a review of the implementation of this section; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b37f-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/c/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" consult with Indian Tribes, Indian industrial entities, and other stakeholders regarding methods to facilitate compliance with—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b380-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/c/6/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" this section; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b381-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/c/6/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" other small business or procurement goals.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6210b382-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Report","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b383-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 1 year after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2020-12-30"},"text":"December 30, 2020","children":[],"tail":", and not less frequently than once every 2 years thereafter, each of the Secretaries shall submit to the Committee on Indian Affairs of the Senate and the Committee on Natural Resources of the House of Representatives a report describing, during the period covered by the report, the implementation of this section by each of the respective Secretaries."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b384-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Contents","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Each report under this subsection shall include, for each fiscal year during the period covered by the report—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b385-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the names of each agency under the respective jurisdiction of each of the Secretaries to which this section has been applied, and efforts made by additional agencies within the Secretaries’ respective Departments to use the procurement procedures under this Act;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b386-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of the types of purchases made from, and contracts (including any relevant modifications, extensions, or renewals) awarded to, Indian economic enterprises, expressed by agency region;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b387-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a description of the percentage increase or decrease in total dollar value and number of purchases and awards made within each agency region, as compared to the totals of the region for the preceding fiscal year;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b388-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a description of the methods used by applicable contracting officers and employees to conduct market searches to identify qualified Indian economic enterprises;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b389-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of all deviations granted under section 1480.403 of title 48, Code of Federal Regulations (or successor regulations), including a description of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id6210b38a-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/E/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the types of alternative procurement methods used, including any Indian owned businesses reported under other procurement goals; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id6210b38b-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/E/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the dollar value of any awards made pursuant to those deviations;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b38c-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/F"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"F"},"text":"(F)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of all determinations made to provide awards to Indian economic enterprises, including a description of the dollar value of the awards;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b38d-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/G"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"G"},"text":"(G)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" a description or summary of the total number and value of all purchases of, and contracts awarded for, supplies, services, and construction (including the percentage increase or decrease, as compared to the preceding fiscal year) from—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id6210b38e-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/G/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Indian economic enterprises; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id6210b38f-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/G/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" non-Indian economic enterprises;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b390-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/H"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"H"},"text":"(H)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any administrative, procedural, legal, or other barriers to achieving the purposes of this section, together with recommendations for legislative or administrative actions to address those barriers; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id6210b391-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/I"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"I"},"text":"(I)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" for each agency region—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id6210b392-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/I/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the total amount spent on purchases made from, and contracts awarded to, Indian economic enterprises; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id6210b393-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/d/2/I/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a comparison of the amount described in clause (i) to the total amount that the agency region would likely have spent on the same purchases made from a non-Indian economic enterprise or contracts awarded to a non-Indian economic enterprise.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6210b394-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s47/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Goals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Each agency shall establish an annual minimum percentage goal for procurement in compliance with this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6210b395-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1910-06-25/ch431/s23"},"text":"June 25, 1910, ch. 431, § 23","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/861"},"text":"36 Stat. 861","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/581/tII/s206"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–581, title II, § 206","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/2940"},"text":"102 Stat. 2940","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/435/s14"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–435, § 14","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/4572"},"text":"108 Stat. 4572","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/261/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–261, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2020-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 2020","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/3311"},"text":"134 Stat. 3311","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/dA/tVIII/s856/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, div. A, title VIII, § 856(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/2726"},"text":"136 Stat. 2726","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6210b396-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6210b397-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id6210b398-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This Act, referred to in subsec. (d)(2)(A), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1910-06-25/ch431/s23"},"text":"act June 25, 1910, ch. 431, § 23","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/861"},"text":"36 Stat. 861","children":[],"tail":", known as the Buy Indian Act, which is classified to this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id6210b399-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is based on proviso of first sentence of section 23 of act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1910-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1910","children":[],"tail":". Remainder of first sentence of section 23 was classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s93"},"text":"section 93 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-10-10/ch851/s4"},"text":"act Oct. 10, 1940, ch. 851, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/1112"},"text":"54 Stat. 1112","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id6210b39a-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1908-04-30/ch153"},"text":"act Apr. 30, 1908, ch. 153","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/35/71"},"text":"35 Stat. 71","children":[],"tail":", making appropriations for the Indian Department."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id6210b39b-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s4902/c"},"text":"section 4902(c) of title 10","children":[],"tail":"” for “section 831(c) of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 1991 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2302"},"text":"10 U.S.C. 2302","children":[],"tail":" note; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/510"},"text":"Public Law 101–510","children":[],"tail":")”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2020—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/261/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–261, § 4","children":[],"tail":", amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section related to employment of Indian labor and purchase of products of Indian industry and participation in Mentor-Protege Program."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/435"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–435","children":[],"tail":" inserted at end “Participation in the Mentor-Protege Program established under section 831 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 1991 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2301"},"text":"10 U.S.C. 2301","children":[],"tail":" note) or receipt of assistance pursuant to any developmental assistance agreement authorized under such program shall not render Indian labor or Indian industry ineligible to receive any assistance authorized under this section. For the purposes of this section—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) no determination of affiliation or control (either direct or indirect) may be found between a protege firm and its mentor firm on the basis that the mentor firm has agreed to furnish (or has furnished) to its protege firm pursuant to a mentor-protege agreement any form of developmental assistance described in subsection (f) of section 831 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 1991 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2301"},"text":"10 U.S.C. 2301","children":[],"tail":" note); and"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) the terms ‘protege firm’ and ‘mentor firm’ have the meaning given such terms in subsection (c) of such section 831.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/581"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–581","children":[],"tail":" inserted “(including, but not limited to printing, notwithstanding any other law)” after “products”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id6213239c-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id6213239d-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions of other officers, employees, and agencies of Department of the Interior, with certain exceptions, to Secretary of the Interior, with power to delegate, see Reorg. Plan No. 3 of 1950, §§ 1, 2, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1950","children":[],"tail":", 15 F.R. 3174, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1262"},"text":"64 Stat. 1262","children":[],"tail":", set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
